</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8aed" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">SEPA's impact is vast, overseeing various sectors, including water, air, land, and climate change. Some key statistics highlighting SEPA’s importance are:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">SEPA monitors over 10,000 industrial sites across Scotland.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">In 2020, SEPA processed over 7,000 environmental permit applications.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">SEPA’s flood warning services protect more than 25,000 properties.






</li></ul><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-30_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These figures illustrate SEPA's extensive role in safeguarding Scotland's environment and the significance of compliance with its regulations.




























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Environmental permits</strong> -  Are licences issued by SEPA to regulate activities that could impact the environment and ensure they are managed sustainably.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulated sites</strong> - Locations that require oversight due to their potential environmental impact, such as industrial facilities, waste management sites, and agricultural operations.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Flood warning services</strong> - Alerts and information provided by SEPA to help communities prepare for and respond to flooding events.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">SEPA's key functions
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Environmental regulation </strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">SEPA regulates activities that could harm the environment by issuing permits and ensuring compliance with environmental laws. This includes monitoring air and water quality, managing waste, and controlling pollution from industrial and agricultural sources.





























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Climate change mitigation
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">SEPA plays a pivotal role in Scotland's efforts to tackle climate change. It supports initiatives to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, promotes renewable energy, and provides guidance on climate adaptation strategies.





























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Flood risk management
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">SEPA is responsible for flood forecasting and warning services, which are essential for protecting communities from the impacts of flooding. This involves working closely with local authorities and other stakeholders to develop flood risk management plans.






























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Environmental crime enforcement
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">SEPA actively combats environmental crime, such as illegal waste disposal and water pollution. It has enforcement powers to investigate and prosecute offenders, ensuring that environmental laws are upheld.































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-63_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-64_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for compliance
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Understanding legislation </strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Organisations must be familiar with the key pieces of legislation that SEPA enforces, including:






























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-71_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-72_ pf-text-1"><strong>Environmental Protection Act 1990</strong> - Provides the framework for managing waste and controlling emissions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-74_ pf-text-1"><strong>Water Environment (Controlled Activities) (Scotland) Regulations 2011</strong> - Governs activities that affect Scotland's water environment.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Pollution Prevention and Control (Scotland) Regulations 2012</strong> - Regulates industrial emissions to prevent pollution.






</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-78_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Implementing compliance strategies
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-80_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To ensure compliance with SEPA regulations, organisations should:































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-82_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-83_ pf-text-1"><strong>Conduct regular audits </strong>- Regular environmental audits help identify areas of non-compliance and opportunities for improvement.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-85_ pf-text-1"><strong>Develop Environmental Management Systems (EMS)</strong> - Implementing an EMS such as ISO 14001 can help organisations manage their environmental responsibilities systematically.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Train staff</strong> - Provide regular training on environmental policies, procedures, and compliance requirements.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-89_ pf-text-1"><strong>Monitor and report</strong> - Establish robust monitoring and reporting systems to track environmental performance and ensure transparency.







</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-91_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Engaging with SEPA
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-93_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Proactive engagement with SEPA can facilitate better compliance. Organisations should:
































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-95_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-96_ pf-text-1"><strong>Maintain open communication</strong> - Regularly communicate with SEPA to stay informed about regulatory updates and best practices.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-98_ pf-text-1"><strong>Seek guidance</strong> - Take advantage of SEPA’s advisory services to gain insights into compliance strategies and environmental management.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-100_ pf-text-1"><strong>Participate in initiatives </strong>- Engage in SEPA-led initiatives and partnerships to improve environmental outcomes.








